$ Registry: HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\.ext

The key `HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\.ext` allows to associate a file type (which apparently is identified by its file name extension such as `.mp3`, `.txt` or more generally `.ext`) with an (existing) application. This application
is identified by *ProgId* which is stored in the → Windows/registry[registry] under → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT/ProgId[`HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\ProgId`].

The *ProgId* is determined by the *default value* of `HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\.ext`.

